cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.NI, cs.GT. 

This paper presents a distributed algorithm for the Minimum Weight Vertex Cover problem, which is a problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves graph theory and approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity). The CONGEST model, which is used in the paper, is a common model in network algorithms, so cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possibility. Finally, the paper involves optimization and approximation, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
